text: Elina Netšajeva (anglicised: Elina Nechayeva; born 10 November 1991) is an Estonian singer, soprano and theatre actress. == Background == In 2007, she participated in the Estonian version of Pop Idol. She graduated from Tallinn French School in 2011 and later the Estonian Academy of Music and Theatre. == Eurovision Song Contest == On 3 March 2018, by winning Eesti Laul 2018, Nechayeva was selected to represent Estonia in the Eurovision Song Contest 2018 with her Italian language song "La forza". At Eurovision, she finished in 8th place out of the 26 finalists. In 2020, Nechayeva was one of the "Eurovision stars" who appeared in the movie Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga. == Discography == === Singles === * La forza (2018) * La voce dell'alba (2019) === Albums === * The Sound of Beauty (2021) == Filmography & acting roles == === Movie === * Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga (as herself) === Television === Television appearances as herself Year Title Role Notes 2007 Estonia is Searching for a Superstar Contestant 2017 Eesti Laul 2017 Semi-final host 2018 Eesti Laul 2018 Contestant Winner Eurovision Song Contest 2018 Estonian contestant 8th place 2020 Masked Singer Estonia Celebrity contestant Runner-up === Theatre roles === Title Role L’elisir d’amore Giannetta The Count of Luxembourg L’enfant et les sortileges Orpheus in the Underworld Eurydike My Fair Lady Eliza Doolittle Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Estonian singers Category:Estonian television actors Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
